                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>&#34;Jerusalem &#40;Holy City&#41; the Glory of all Lands.&#34;¬ù<lb/>
                ALFRED A. MARCUS&#44;<lb/>
                Diamond Merchant and Importer&#44;<lb/>
                Purchaser of Real Estate&#44; &#40;Landed Property.&#41;<lb/>
                Residence&#44; 127 DARTMOUTH STREET.<lb/></p>
            <p>No business will be transacted or interviews had on the Jewish Sabbath&#44; from one hour before sunset on<lb/> Friday until one hour after sunset on Saturday&#44; or on the Jewish Festivals&#44; and no letters will be opened on<lb/> those days.<lb/></p>
            <p>Boston&#44; Ab 13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> AM 5641.<lb/></p>
            <p>My very dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Your&#39;s of yesterday received &#38;<lb/> in reply would state I am most sanguine<lb/> of success &#40;Behold the Guardian of<lb/> Israel neither sleeps nor slumbers&#41;<lb/> &#38; the Almighty God watches over us.<lb/>  I never met a man whose principals<lb/> from what I have read about you<lb/> are so near my views as your&#39;s<lb/> and may our most heavenly father<lb/> grant your sincere wishes be realised.<lb/>  I must tell you most frankly &#38;<lb/> honestly it is my <sic>heartful</sic> ambition<lb/> that within the next seven weeks<lb/> or less time I may have the great<lb/> joy of liquidating the entire<lb/> amount of your indebtedness&#44; but<lb/> of course I am mortal &#38; of the<lb/></p> 
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>most sanguine disposition I have<lb/> several very large &#38; most valuable<lb/> pieces of Real Estate in Boston.<lb/>  I could by the sale at a fair &#38; reasona<lb/> price by the disposal of some easily<lb/> do all you would desire I also<lb/> have several interest in M&#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/> Stock &#38; Water Power Bonds &#38; as<lb/> fair a prospect as any one with<lb/> God Blessing.  I do not know at<lb/> this moment a greater born that<lb/> a mortal could do than assist to<lb/> discharge your shule debt for<lb/> more reasons than one I do not<lb/> wish <hi rend="underline">my name</hi> known at present<lb/> but when the proper time comes will<lb/> let you know.  Regarding that Blessed dear<lb/> Sir Moses at his advanced years it could<lb/> hardly be expected for him to respond.<lb/>  I received a very affectionate note this<lb/> morng from Baron de Worms&#44; in acknowd<lb/> of a small sum we sent to relieve our<lb/> brethren in Russia.  Mrs. Marcus thank<lb/> God is gradually improving God Bless<lb/> you from your&#39;s most truly Alfred A Marcus<lb/></p>
        </body>
